content.description:
A reusable component for rendering individual fields/properties within a [view-spec](item://bbbbbbbb-0000-0000-0000-000000000000). Field-views are the building blocks of declarative views.

## The Render Function

Field-views export a `render` function with a different signature than item views:

```javascript
export async function render(value, options, api) {
  // value: the field's current value
  // options: { label, mode, onChange, field, item, ... }
  // api: the renderer API

  const wrapper = api.createElement('div', { className: 'my-field' });
  // ... build UI ...
  return wrapper;
}
```

## Options Parameter

| Property | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `label` | Human-readable label from ui_hint |
| `mode` | `"readonly"` or `"editable"` |
| `onChange` | Callback to save changes: `onChange(newValue)` |
| `field` | Field path (e.g., `"title"`) |
| `item` | The full item being rendered |
| `scrollToLine` | For code fields: line to scroll to |
| `scrollToRegion` | For code/markdown: named region to highlight |

## Editable Mode

In editable mode, call `options.onChange(newValue)` to persist changes:

```javascript
export async function render(value, options, api) {
  const { label, mode, onChange } = options;

  if (mode === 'editable') {
    const input = api.createElement('input', { 
      type: 'text', 
      value: value || '' 
    });
    input.onblur = () => onChange(input.value);
    return input;
  } else {
    const span = api.createElement('span');
    span.textContent = value || '';
    return span;
  }
}
```

## Creating a Custom Field-View

```javascript
{
  id: crypto.randomUUID(),
  name: "field-view-color-picker",
  type: "cccccccc-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",  // field-view
  content: {
    description: "Color picker for hex color values",
    code: `
      export async function render(value, options, api) {
        const { label, mode, onChange } = options;
        const wrapper = api.createElement('div');

        if (label) {
          const labelEl = api.createElement('label');
          labelEl.textContent = label;
          wrapper.appendChild(labelEl);
        }

        if (mode === 'editable') {
          const input = api.createElement('input', { type: 'color' });
          input.value = value || '#000000';
          input.onchange = () => onChange(input.value);
          wrapper.appendChild(input);
        } else {
          const swatch = api.createElement('div');
          swatch.style.cssText = \`
            width: 24px; height: 24px; 
            background: \${value || '#000'};
            border-radius: 4px;
          \`;
          wrapper.appendChild(swatch);
        }

        return wrapper;
      }
    `
  }
}
```

Then use in a view-spec:

```javascript
ui_hints: [
  { field: "themeColor", label: "Theme", component: "color-picker", mode: "editable" }
]
```

## Standard Field-Views

| Name | File | Purpose |
|------|------|--------|
| `field-view-text` | [item](item://c116c28d-0903-4fc7-8534-e1c4f245f55d) | Single-line text |
| `field-view-markdown-readonly` | [item](item://8fd956ff-01f4-48f5-8afb-42fc2718005b) | Rendered markdown display |
| `field-view-markdown-editable` | [item](item://56f77a00-baf5-43cc-9dc4-8ad0c66f1e8f) | CodeMirror markdown editor |
| `field-view-code-readonly` | [item](item://8e2f3e95-cc2d-44a3-beeb-0569f400da7c) | Syntax-highlighted code |
| `field-view-code-editable` | [item](item://3c5b0b26-863d-413b-b32e-e1189007b450) | CodeMirror code editor |
| `field-view-checkbox` | [item](item://70b84e74-f079-4fa0-84c6-bb8d3ab31f61) | Boolean checkbox |

